SOME EXAMPLES AND BENCHMARKS FOR CIAO

NOTE: Most of the code here are benchmarks that run in all Ciao
  backends.

  Compile 'testsuite_{1..4}' with your preferred compiler.
  Using the 'target-platform' option you can select the UI version.
  
  $ ciaotool js-backend --target-platform chrome try-exec testsuite_1

  or the command-line version (using NodeJS):
  
  $ ciaotool js-backend --target-platform nodejs try-exec testsuite_1

Compiling the Prolog->JS compiler
=================================

 - include optim_comp in your path

   $ cd OPTIM_COMP_DIR
   $ eval `./ciaotool bash-env`

 - compile optim_comp:

   $ ciaotool update-all

 - and compile the ptojs backend with

   $ ciaotool update-comp-js

Testing the Prolog->JS compiler
===============================

 - go to the example directory

 - execute a single program with:

   $ ciaotool js-backend --target-platform evalmod-nodejs PROGRAM

 - or execute the tests:

   $ ciaotool js-backend check-all

